The President welcomed the Air Force Academy football team, the Falcons, to the White House for a ceremony. He recognized several military officials in attendance and praised the team's accomplishments. The President highlighted their wins against Navy, Army, and Colorado and commended their record-breaking performances. He emphasized the importance of teamwork and service and presented the team with the Commander-in-Chief's trophy. The President concluded by expressing his gratitude to the team and their families and handed over the microphone to Coach Calhoun, who thanked the President and praised the leadership at the Air Force Academy. The team captains then presented the President with an Air Force Falcons jersey, football, and helmet.